<HEADLINE> Suit filed on behalf of three plane crash victims  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WILKES-BARRE, Pa. (AP) - A lawyer representing the estates of
three people who died in last month's casino junket plane crash has
filed suit against the operator of the charter plane.
</P>
<P>
   Joseph Quinn Jr. filed suit Wednesday on behalf of the estates
of Joan Fumanti, Bernard M. Kachinko Sr. and Diane Schwartz.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have our people lined up,'' Quinn said. ''As soon as the
airframe (of the plane) is returned from the manufacturer, we want
to inspect it immediately.''
</P>
