other families of crash victims to pursue lawsuits against
Executive Airlines and related companies.
</P>
<P>
   Both pilots and all 17 passengers were killed on May 21 when an
Executive Airlines charter plane crashed into a mountain while on
approach to the Wilkes-Barre/Scranton International Airport.
</P>
<P>
   The National Transportation Safety Board is still trying to
determine the cause of the crash. Investigators have been hampered
because the cockpit voice recorder was not working. In addition,
the plane was not equipped with a flight data recorder; none was
required.
