<HEADLINE> Pitcher Optioned 1 Day After Recall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- In a move that paves the way for the promotion of
top prospect Tomo Ohka, who pitched a perfect game for Pawtucket on
June 1, the Boston Red Sox returned lefty reliever Tim Young to the
International League team Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Ohka is expected to start Friday night in Toronto, taking the
spot of Jeff Fassero who was placed on the disabled list Monday
with weakness in his left shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Ohka became the third player in the 117-year history of the
International League to pitch a perfect game. He was 6-5 with a
2.73 ERA for Pawtucket.
</P>
<P>
   Ohka was a combined 15-0 with Double-A Trenton and Triple-A
Pawtucket last season, his first in U.S. professional baseball,
before being promoted to Boston, where he was 1-2. He played
professionally in his native Japan in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Young had been recalled from Pawtucket on Tuesday and didn't
pitch for Boston before being optioned.
</P>
</TEXT>
