<HEADLINE> Clinton Has Fun With Lockhart Photo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Nice hair? Nice legs? Clean feet? Alert?
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton scribbled those questions on an aging
photograph of an unrecognizable, bushy-haired man asleep or
unconscious on a chaise longue, barefoot with a pair of flip-flop
sandals at his side. A mug sits next to the recliner.
</P>
<P>
   ''Memo from the president. Attention. Who is this man?'' the
president scrawled on the picture.
</P>
<P>
   Turns out it was a much younger Joe Lockhart, now the
president's press secretary.
</P>
<P>
   ''He looks like he's been knocked out because he put his hand in
an electrical circuit,'' Clinton said, showing off the Lockhart
photo during a surprise visit to the press briefing room Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton said a buddy of Lockhart's gave him the picture last
week in Texas. The president had it framed and brought it to the
briefing room to find a home.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think I'll put it right here (on the lectern),'' Clinton
said. ''This is the Joe Lockhart memorial podium. I love it. He'll
never forgive me for showing it.'' The president eventually was
persuaded that the photo belonged on a hallway wall leading into
the press office.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton's inscription said: ''He's practicing for his life's
work -- being White House press secretary -- the president's
finest.''
</P>
</TEXT>
