<HEADLINE> American Man Kills Child, Self  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Russia (AP) -- An American man visiting St.
Petersburg threw his 5-month-old daughter out of a 16th-floor
window and then jumped to his death after her, police and consulate
officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Police were treating the deaths Wednesday as a murder-suicide,
consulate spokesman Tom Leary said.
</P>
<P>
   The man came to Russia on a tourist visa June 4 with his wife
and daughter, said Vyacheslav Stepchenko of the St. Petersburg
police. The child had been ill because of injuries suffered during
birth, Stepchenko said.
</P>
<P>
   The wife is a U.S. resident of Russian descent, Leary said.
</P>
<P>
   Their names were not released.
</P>
