<HEADLINE> 'Sports Night' Won't Be Back  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ''Sports Night'' has had its day.
</P>
<P>
   The producers of the sitcom canceled by ABC said they have
decided not to move it to another network despite several
''intriguing offers.''
</P>
<P>
   ''We are tremendously proud of the two seasons' worth of
episodes that aired on ABC and felt committed to reviving the show
only if this creative integrity could continue,'' series creator
Aaron Sorkin and executive producer Thomas Schlamme said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   There were reports that HBO or another cable channel might pick
up the series.
</P>
<P>
   ''Sports Night,'' a behind-the-scenes look at an ESPN-style news
show, starred Peter Krause and Josh Charles as the anchormen,
Felicity Huffman as their producer and Robert Guillaume as the
boss.
</P>
<P>
   The show won more critical acclaim than viewers, unlike Sorkin's
White House drama ''The West Wing,'' which is a hit on NBC.
</P>
</TEXT>
