<HEADLINE> Backstreet Boy Kevin Gets Married  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Ky. (AP) -- Backstreet Boy Kevin Richardson is officially
off the market.
</P>
<P>
   The 27-year-old singer married longtime girlfriend Kristin
Willits on Saturday, his brother Tim Richardson confirmed
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Tim, a minister, performed the ceremony at a church camp once
managed by the brothers' late father, Jerald. Another brother,
Jerald Jr., was best man.
</P>
<P>
   It was a ''beautiful, simple ceremony,'' free of paparazzi and
circling helicopters, Tim Richardson said.
</P>
<P>
   Among the 150 to 200 friends and relatives who attended were
cousin and Backstreet Boy Brian Littrell, who announced his own
engagement earlier this year, and the three other members of the
group: Howie Dorough, Nick Carter and A.J. McLean.
</P>
<P>
   The newlyweds are expected to have a more public celebration
later this year in Los Angeles.
</P>
