<HEADLINE> Film Features Mellencamp As Actor  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) -- The low-budget film ''After Image'' will
feature John Mellencamp -- as an actor only.
</P>
<P>
   The rocker's songs won't be used for the movie score, which is
being composed by former Rochester resident Richard Tuttobene.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, the movie is a mostly Rochester affair. Most of the
filming, which ended Wednesday, was done in the city, and the film
is directed by Bob Manganelli, a 1983 graduate of Rochester
Institute of Technology.
</P>
<P>
   ''It wouldn't have been possible to do this film in New York or
Los Angeles for $1.4 million,'' publicist Angelo Mancuso told the
Rochester Democrat and Chronicle.
</P>
<P>
   Mellencamp plays a disillusioned police photographer returning
to Rochester to live with his aunt. He falls in love with a woman
whose psychic powers soon entangle them with an ominous killer.
</P>
