<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 18:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drowned pit bull marks latest in series of dog killings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OCEAN CITY, N.J. (AP) - A pit bull drowned after being thrown
into a bay in a weighted container, marking the latest in a rash of
similar killings in southern New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
   The full-grown 50-pound female had been put in the portable dog
carrier and weighted down with about 20 pounds worth of rocks and
chunks of asphalt, police said.
</P>
<P>
   A boat ramp attendant discovered the animal in the water about 7
a.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''You've got to be pretty twisted to do something like this.
This is just terrible,'' said Mark Pulvino, dog manager for the
Humane Society of Ocean City.
</P>
<P>
   A $500 reward has been offered by the Humane Society for the
arrest and conviction of the person or people responsible. No
arrests have been made, police said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   In just over a month, four pit bulls have been found dead in
Bridgeton under mysterious circumstances:
</P>
<P>
   -On May 19, two pit bulls were found hanging from their leashes
in a tree.
</P>
<P>
   -On June 3, a dead pit bull that appeared to have been hanged
was found in the back yard of a home. The dog didn't belong to the
people who lived at the house.
</P>
<P>
   -On Sunday, a Cohansey River fisherman found a pit bull that
drowned after being thrown into the river, an 8-pound rock fastened
to the rope around its neck.
</P>
<P>
   There were developments Thursday in two of those cases. Two men
pleaded guilty to animal cruelty in connection with the May 19
hangings.
</P>
<P>
   Bernard Green, 19, and Donray Crawford, 21, both of Bridgeton,
were sentenced to 90 days in jail, fined $500, ordered to undergo
counseling and to perform 30 days community service at the
Cumberland County Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals
shelter.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, Municipal Court Judge Laura Scruggs ordered both
men to witness the euthanizing of two animals at the shelter.
</P>
<P>
   ''Generally, the deaths of these pit bulls involve dogs that
will not fight,'' said Bev Greco, an SPCA cruelty investigator.
''That's why these people acquire these animals in the first place,
to fight. They don't find out until the dogs are over six months
old that they're not aggressive enough and won't fight, so they
decide, for whatever reason, to kill them.''
</P>
<P>
   Also Thursday, police arrested the owner of the pit bull found
drowned Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Lawrence Spencer, 27, of Bridgeton, was charged with animal
cruelty and released on a summons. He told police the dog was
sickly, so he tied a weight around the neck and threw it into the
river, according to police Lt. Greg Everingham.
</P>
<P>
   ''For $35, he could have called the SPCA. Now, he's staring down
the barrel of the same kind of sentences these guys got today.
These things just defy logic,'' Everingham said.
</P>
<P>
   Ocean City police have asked Bridgeton police to compare notes
from their investigations to see if the killings are related,
Everingham said. Right now, it is not believed that they are, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   But Pulvino believes there is a correlation.
</P>
<P>
   ''I do believe this is related to the Bridgeton one. Either that
or it's a copycat,'' Pulvino said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-06-22-00 1835 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000622.0157 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 18:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Concerned Over Gas Prices  </HEADLINE>
By H. JOSEF HEBERT
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- With gasoline and crude prices soaring,
President Clinton expressed concern Thursday that high world oil
prices of more than $30 a barrel will ''rifle throughout the
economy'' if not contained.
</P>
<P>
   The president said that oil prices should be in the $20 to $25 a
barrel range, well below what they are. Despite a decision by OPEC
oil ministers to modestly boost production, crude prices shot up
Thursday to more than $32 a barrel and some analysts said $40 was
no longer unthinkable.
</P>
<P>
   Industry executives have said that the record gasoline prices,
averaging $1.68 a gallon nationwide and more than $2 in parts of
the Midwest, are partly due to the high cost of crude oil, which
accounts for 43 percent the cost of a gallon of gasoline.
</P>
<P>
   The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries agreed on
Wednesday to boost production by about 700,000 barrels a day, a
modest amount that was not expected to have strong impact on U.S.
retail fuel prices.
</P>
<P>
   The market dismissed the OPEC overture. West Texas Intermediate
crude for August delivery moved 82 cents higher Thursday to $32.19
a barrel. The 10-year high was $34.37 a barrel in March.
</P>
<P>
   While the $2 plus a gallon gasoline prices in the
Chicago-Milwaukee area has caught the headlines, Clinton said he
was concerned that high crude oil prices also are pushing up fuel
prices for truckers and airlines.
</P>
<P>
   ''So this is going to rifle throughout the economy,'' said
Clinton, speaking to reporters on the South Lawn before departing
for Arizona and California. He said it was ''in the best interest
of the people of the Untied States, but also the oil-producing
countries'' to have prices stabilize in the $20 to $25 a barrel
range.
</P>
<P>
   But Clinton said the high cost of crude 'doesn't explain by a
long stretch'' the sharp increase in gasoline prices in parts of
the Midwest, and ''neither does the requirement for special
additives to reduce air pollution.''
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Trade Commission, which has begun a formal
investigation into retail gasoline prices, will focus on the wide
difference in price of cleaner burning gasoline -- required since
June 1 in areas with severe summer smog -- and conventional
gasoline. The cleaner fuel has been cited repeatedly by the oil
industry as the reason for much of the price increase in the
Chicago and Milwaukee areas.
</P>
<P>
   FTC Chairman Robert Pitofsky told reporters Thursday that the
''high price differential'' between the new blend of cleaner
gasoline and conventional fuel ''has raised significant questions
... that can only be answered with a thorough investigation.''
</P>
<P>
   He declined to discuss the investigation further, but said the
FTC would issue an interim report within a month.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, wholesale gasoline prices in the Chicago and
Milwaukee areas have dropped in some areas by about 25 cents a
gallon over the last week, while retail prices have increased
several cents, remaining over $2 a gallon, according to figures
cited by the Environmental Protection Agency.
</P>
<P>
   The figures are from surveys conducted by OPIS Energy Group, a
private company that tracks national energy prices in detail.
</P>
<P>
   High energy costs, and particularly gasoline prices, continued
to produce finger pointing by members of Congress and the campaigns
of both Gov. George W. Bush and Vice President Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
   Bush and a string of Republicans in Congress blamed the Clinton
administration of failing to stand up to OPEC countries and
pursuing an energy policy that thwarts domestic oil production.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's really being driven by the fact that we're just dependent
on OPEC oil,'' Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott, R-Miss., told
reporters, accusing the president of ''groping'' for an answer to
high energy prices. He said ways have to be found for more domestic
production, including opening up an Alaska arctic refuge to oil
drilling.
</P>
<P>
   Gore suggested price gouging. ''Big oil may have gotten too
big,'' he said, adding quickly that he was not suggesting a breakup
of oil companies. And Clinton reeled off a string of initiatives he
said he had sent to Congress to spur energy conservation, but which
the Republican-led Congress has ignored.
</P>
<P>
   Oil industry spokesmen denied any companies are involved in
illegal pricing activities. ''The market is working. The (gasoline)
prices are falling,'' said Red Cavaney, president of the American
Petroleum Institute.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   AAA nationwide gasoline price charts:
http://aaa.com/news12/prmain.html
</P>
<P>
   Energy Information Administration: http://www.eia.doe.gov
</P>
<P>
