<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grand jury indicts Queens man in Central Park attacks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A grand jury indicted an 18-year-old man on
Thursday in connection with the June 11 attacks on dozens of women
in Central Park, a spokeswoman for the Manhattan district attorney
said.
</P>
<P>
   Lonnie Hopson, of Queens, was indicted on charges of
first-degree sexual abuse and first-degree riot, said DA
spokeswoman Barbara Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   Hopson remains jailed on $10,000 bail, Thompson said. He is next
due in court on July 10.
</P>
<P>
   Nine men have been indicted by the grand jury in connection with
the assaults. Police have arrested 20 men in the attacks.
</P>
<P>
   Fifty-three women have told police they were doused with water,
chased, stripped, molested or assaulted. Several others have
reported being victims of robberies or attempted robberies.
</P>
<P>
   Police Commissioner Howard Safir has said police are conducting
an internal investigation into allegations that some officers
ignored victims' pleas for help. He warned that police officers
could be fired if investigators prove the allegations are true.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   NYPD Central Park photos:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.nyclink.org/html/nypd/html/wanted/wantedcp.html
</P>
</TEXT>
