<HEADLINE> Astros' Powell Goes To DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Houston Astros right-handed reliever Jay Powell
was placed on the 15-day disabled list, retroactive to Monday, with
tendinitis in his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Powell, 1-1 with a 4.70 ERA in 23 innings over 26 games, was on
the DL with the same ailment from May 17 through June 3.
</P>
<P>
   Since returning, he was 1-0 in 4 2-3 innings of four games,
giving up five hits and four runs.
</P>
<P>
   He last pitched Sunday at San Francisco. On Tuesday, he
attempted to warm up before the game at Enron Field with the
Dodgers, but complained of pain in his shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Right-hander Mike Maddux was activated from the DL to replace
Powell. Maddux missed 29 games since going on the DL May 21 with a
strained right groin.
</P>
<P>
   He is 2-2 with a 5.48 ERA in 18 appearances.
</P>
