<HEADLINE> Yanks' Knoblauch Has Another Error  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- New York Yankees second baseman Chuck Knoblauch,
who has had trouble making the short throw to first base, made
another error on Thursday night -- his 14th of the season and his
fifth in eight games.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Offerman hit a fourth-inning grounder to Knoblauch, who
fielded it cleanly but threw well wide of first baseman Tino
Martinez. The ball rolled all the way to the wall behind home
plate, and Offerman went to second as the Boston crowd taunted
Knoblauch.
</P>
<P>
   Knoblauch was a Gold Glove winner in 1997, but his defense has
deteriorated since then -- especially on the seemingly simple throw
to first.
</P>
<P>
   The three previous batters all grounded the ball to Knoblauch,
but he made those plays without incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
