<HEADLINE> Hentrich, Kinchen Leading Classic  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLIFTON, N.J. (AP) -- Tennessee punter Craig Hentrich shot a
3-under-par 69 on Thursday to share the second-round lead with
Carolina tight end Brian Kinchen in NFL players' portion of the
Cadillac NFL Golf Classic.
</P>
<P>
   Kinchen, a three-time runner-up, had a 71 to match Hentrich at
3-over 147 on the Upper Montclair Golf Club course.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee kicker Al Del Greco, the defending champion and
five-time winner, was a stroke back along with Carolina fullback
Chris Hetherington. Del Greco, who also won in 1993, '94, '95, '96,
had his second straight 74. Hetherington ballooned to a 78, eight
shots more than his first round.
</P>
<P>
   The low 26 players in the 56-man field advanced to Friday's
third round, where scoring starts over. The low 12 players Friday
will advance to the final round Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterbacks Casey Weldon (153), Shane Matthews (154) and Glenn
Foley (155) were the next closest after 36 holes.
</P>
<P>
   San Francisco wide receiver Jerry Rice (156) qualified for
Friday's play, but withdraw because of personal reasons, allowing
former New York Giants cornerback Phillippi Sparks (169) to make
the cut.
</P>
</TEXT>
