<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 21:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bills increasing legal age to buy handguns advance  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Lawmakers moved closer Thursday to pushing
the legal age to buy handguns in New Jersey to 21.
</P>
<P>
   The bill to do that cleared the Law and Public Safety Committee
and now moves to the full Assembly for a vote.
</P>
<P>
   The state Senate voted May 18 to approve the age increase in a
package of bills sponsors said would increase gun safety. Other
measures approved by the Senate would mandate handguns to have
features that allow only a gun's owner to fire the weapon; require
all new guns to undergo ballistics tests and spend $5 million to
supplement enforcement efforts.
</P>
<P>
   Included in the bill passed by the Assembly committee are
criminal penalties for violating the age limit. The current legal
age is 18.
</P>
<P>
   People who knowingly sell a gun to a person under 21 could be
sentenced to up to five years in prison and face $15,000 in fines.
If someone under 21 buys a gun, the penalty would be up to 18
months and a fine of $10,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
