<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Ties Schmidt's Homer Mark  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire tied Mike Schmidt for seventh on
the career home run list, hitting No. 548 in the fourth inning
against the San Francisco Giants on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire's first homer in three days was the Cardinals' first hit
off Shawn Estes. It came on a 2-0 pitch, and traveled an estimated
475 feet to straightaway center. McGwire has 101 homers and 214
RBIs in 212 career games at Busch Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   With his 26th homer of the season, McGwire also pulled into a
tie with Barry Bonds of the Giants for the major league lead. He is
on pace to hit 59 homers after hitting 65 last year and a record 70
in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire, who took a called third strike that ended the first,
reached 548 homers in 5,832 at-bats. It took Schmidt 8,352 at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this season, McGwire passed Jimmie Foxx (534) and Mickey
Mantle (536). Reggie Jackson is sixth on the career list with 563.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
