<HEADLINE> Lynx 86, Starzz 64  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Katie Smith scored 21 points and Betty Lennox
added 19 as the Minnesota Lynx beat Utah 86-64 Thursday night,
snapping the Starzz's four-game winning streak.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota (7-4), which had lost its last two games, including
being held to a season-low 55 points at home by Phoenix on Tuesday,
opened the game with an 11-2 run. The Lynx led by at least 10
points for the game's final 33 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   It was the second straight game the Starzz (7-6) played without
star forward Natalie Williams. Utah beat Seattle on Tuesday without
Williams, who is sitting out after straining her back on Sunday,
but the Starzz didn't have the offense to keep pace with Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Coming off her worst offensive performance of the season -- 10
points on 4-of-15 shooting against Phoenix -- Smith had 14 points in
the first half as the Lynx led by 21 points at halftime. Lennox
scored all but four of her points in the first half.
</P>
